▎ "It starts by giving the model one job and one identity. It's a scriptwriter for a channel where 'a tradition-keeper reveals lost knowledge that industry buried for profit.' That one sentence is doing a lot — it sets the genre, the narrator type, and the villain framing all at once. And right after, I tell it to write the spoken script only — no headers, no stage directions, no markdown. That matters, because by default the model wants to give you a formatted outline. We want one person talking to camera."

