▎ "Beat one — the cold open. It puts you, the viewer, into your own discomfort in present tense, with a running clock and at least three hard numbers. That's retention engineering. You win or lose a YouTube viewer in the first fifteen seconds, and '142 degrees, it's 2 p.m., you set it to 68' grabs harder than any intro."
▎
▎ [Highlight beat 2]
▎
▎ "Beat two — authority comes from tradition, not credentials. 'I've never paid an electric bill, not once.' The audience for this content distrusts experts — that's the whole premise — so credibility has to come from lineage and self-reliance instead of a degree."

2:15 — Beat 8, the credibility hinge

▎ [Screen: highlight beat 8 — THE MONEY TRAIL]
▎
▎ "This is the one I want you to really notice. Beat eight is where you name who profits. And the instruction explicitly tells the model to deny a grand conspiracy — 'there was no meeting' — and replace it with something quieter: everyone who profits just tacitly agrees not to mention it. That's the single most important line in the whole prompt. The moment you claim a secret cabal, you lose the smart half of your audience. 'Nobody's hiding it, they're just all quietly not telling you' is both believable and impossible to disprove. That restraint is what makes the format work."

