▎ "Below the beats are the style rules that apply everywhere. The big one is 'specificity is the whole product' — always pick an exact number, year, or name over a vague one, because specifics read as testimony and vague claims read as opinion. There's 'mind-read the viewer's next thought, then answer it.' There's the two-step where you name the real scientific mechanism for authority, then immediately translate it back to plain folk language for warmth. And 'anti-helplessness' — every section has to end in something cheap the viewer can actually do, because the emotion we're selling is empowerment, not despair."

