▎ "And the last piece — the accuracy guardrail. I told the model to keep the actual mechanisms physically true and safe, and to soften a claim rather than fabricate fake studies or fake experts. Two reasons. One, this content tells real people to climb into attics and cut things — false advice is a liability. Two, these channels get torn apart in the comments when a claim is wrong. The drama lives in the framing — the villain, the grievance, the hidden knowledge — not in fake physics. Keeping the science honest actually makes the channel harder to debunk."

